**Abstract:**
Working notes dated October 10, 1996 on "Speculative and Practical Reason or Intellect." Opens with extended Latin quotation from Aquinas's Peri Hermeneias commentary. Critiques Aristotle's conflation of practical and speculative knowledge, arguing the continuity between them is confused. Questions whether intellectus can refer univocally to both practical and speculative faculties.

**AI Recommendation:** Precedes 96-OCT-2; working notes toward epistemological critique of Greek tradition.

